      "writtenOn": "2026-04-15T19:22:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed. I reverted rx_queue registration to always start as POLLING. Drivers that want the global default now pass VNET_HW_IF_RX_MODE_DEFAULT to vnet_hw_if_set_rx_queue_mode(), which resolves to hi-\u003edefault_rx_mode. Since initial mode is always POLLING, the rx_mode_change_function callback is always invoked when the default differs, so the driver can set up interrupt handling or reject unsupported modes. Drivers that don\u0027t call set_rx_queue_mode (dpdk, vmxnet3, af_xdp) are unaffected, they keep POLLING from registration.",
      "parentUuid": "5e7f1d18_90edfe90",
      "revId": "2656c60213b67af475551759e031b32d2c854e1a",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
